POLAND’S ELECTION SHOCKER RATTLES EUROPE’S CENTRIST COMFORT ZONE Poland just delivered another blow to Europe's establishment as Conservative Karol Nawrocki beat PM Donald Tusk's handpicked centrist Rafal Trzaskowski in the presidential race. The victory torpedoes Tusk's reform agenda and sends shockwaves through Brussels, where moderates counted on Polish voters to reject the right at the last minute. They didn't. This marks another domino falling in Europe's populist wave. First Italy, then Netherlands, now Poland joining the conservative resurgence against EU centralism. The continental political realignment continues. Source: ForeignPolicyCom
